<Link id="l01384" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1384"><Highlight kind="normal">  </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">// One of our operands must be on the top of the stack.  If neither is yet, we</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>

<Link id="l01393" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1393"><Highlight kind="normal">    &#125; </Highlight><Highlight kind="keywordflow">else</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"> </Highlight><Highlight kind="keywordflow">if</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"> (KillsOp1) &#123;</Highlight></CodeLine>

<Link id="l01577" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1577"><Highlight kind="normal">  </Highlight><Highlight kind="keywordflow">case</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"> TargetOpcode::INLINEASM&#95;BR: &#123;</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01578" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1578"><Highlight kind="normal">    </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">// The inline asm MachineInstr currently only &#42;uses&#42; FP registers for the</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01579" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1579"><Highlight kind="normal">    </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">// &#39;f&#39; constraint.  These should be turned into the current ST(x) register</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01580" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1580"><Highlight kind="normal">    </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">// in the machine instr.</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01581" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1581"><Highlight kind="normal">    </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">//</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01582" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1582"><Highlight kind="normal">    </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">// There are special rules for x87 inline assembly. The compiler must know</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01583" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1583"><Highlight kind="normal">    </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">// exactly how many registers are popped and pushed implicitly by the asm.</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01584" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1584"><Highlight kind="normal">    </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">// Otherwise it is not possible to restore the stack state after the inline</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01585" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1585"><Highlight kind="normal">    </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">// asm.</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01586" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1586"><Highlight kind="normal">    </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">//</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01587" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1587"><Highlight kind="normal">    </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">// There are 3 kinds of input operands:</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01588" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1588"><Highlight kind="normal">    </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">//</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01589" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1589"><Highlight kind="normal">    </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">// 1 Popped inputs. These must appear at the stack top in ST0-STn. A</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01590" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1590"><Highlight kind="normal">    </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">//    popped input operand must be in a fixed stack slot, and it is either</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01591" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1591"><Highlight kind="normal">    </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">//    tied to an output operand, or in the clobber list. The MI has ST use</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01592" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1592"><Highlight kind="normal">    </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">//    and def operands for these inputs.</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01593" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1593"><Highlight kind="normal">    </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">//</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01594" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1594"><Highlight kind="normal">    </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">// 2 Fixed inputs. These inputs appear in fixed stack slots, but are</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01595" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1595"><Highlight kind="normal">    </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">//    preserved by the inline asm. The fixed stack slots must be STn-STm</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01596" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1596"><Highlight kind="normal">    </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">//    following the popped inputs. A fixed input operand cannot be tied to</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01597" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1597"><Highlight kind="normal">    </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">//    an output or appear in the clobber list. The MI has ST use operands</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01598" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1598"><Highlight kind="normal">    </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">//    and no defs for these inputs.</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01599" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1599"><Highlight kind="normal">    </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">//</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01600" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1600"><Highlight kind="normal">    </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">// 3 Preserved inputs. These inputs use the &quot;f&quot; constraint which is</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01601" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1601"><Highlight kind="normal">    </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">//    represented as an FP register. The inline asm won&#39;t change these</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01602" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1602"><Highlight kind="normal">    </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">//    stack slots.</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01603" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1603"><Highlight kind="normal">    </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">//</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01604" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1604"><Highlight kind="normal">    </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">// Outputs must be in ST registers, FP outputs are not allowed. Clobbered</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01605" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1605"><Highlight kind="normal">    </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">// registers do not count as output operands. The inline asm changes the</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01606" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1606"><Highlight kind="normal">    </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">// stack as if it popped all the popped inputs and then pushed all the</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01607" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1607"><Highlight kind="normal">    </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">// output operands.</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01608" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1608"><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01609" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1609"><Highlight kind="normal">    </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">// Scan the assembly for ST registers used, defined and clobbered. We can</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01610" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1610"><Highlight kind="normal">    </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">// only tell clobbers from defs by looking at the asm descriptor.</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01611" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1611"><Highlight kind="normal">    </Highlight><Highlight kind="keywordtype">unsigned</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"> STUses = 0, STDefs = 0, STClobbers = 0;</Highlight></CodeLine>
